==English==

{{rank|thus|order|near|286|public|others|anything|matter}}

===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[publicus]]'''

===Adjective===
'''public'''

# having to do with the affairs or official affairs of all people, as opposed to just a private group

====Translations====
{{top}}
*Finnish: [[julkinen]], [[yleinen]]
*German: [[öffentlich]]
{{mid}}
*Swedish: [[offentlig]], [[allmän]]
{{bottom}}

===Noun===
'''public'''

# the people in general, regardless of membership of any particular group. A police notice may read ''Members of the public may not proceed beyond this point''

====Antonyms====
*[[private]]

